    // Calculate process capability:
    //   Cp = (USL - LSL) / (6 * std_dev)
    //   Cpk = min((USL - mean) / (3 * std_dev), (mean - LSL) / (3 * std_dev))
    //   Cpk < 1.0 → incapable (fails spec more than expected)
    //   Cpk < 1.33 → marginal
    //   Cpk >= 1.33 → capable
    //   Cpk >= 1.67 → world class
